    "name": "Giant Water Strider",
    "type": "monster",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Description",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "A giant water strider is a long-legged insect with the ability to walk on water. It feeds on fish and birds. Water striders use their weak flight only to escape predators or for seasonal migrations to new breeding areas. They are sometimes kept as mounts by coastdwelling humanoids. A giant water strider lives 1\u20132 years.<br/><br/>Carrying more than a light load (200 pounds) prevents a giant water strider from using its water skating ability."
        }
    ],
    "html": "<i>This bug has long, fuzzy legs that support it on the water\u2019s surface as if the creature stands on solid ground.</i>",
